6837 use_current_size_for_scrollbar_y = true;
6838
6839 // Collapse window by double-clicking on title bar
6840 // At this point we don't have a clipping rectangle setup yet, so we can use the title bar area for hit detection and drawing
6841 if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoCollapse))
6842 {
6843 // We don't use a regular button+id to test for double-click on title bar (mostly due to legacy reason, could be fixed), so verify that we don't have items over the title bar.
6844 ImRect title_bar_rect = window->TitleBarRect();
6845 if (g.HoveredWindow == window && g.HoveredId == 0 && g.HoveredIdPreviousFrame == 0 && IsMouseHoveringRect(title_bar_rect.Min, title_bar_rect.Max))
6846 if (g.IO.MouseClickedCount[0] == 2 && GetKeyOwner(ImGuiKey_MouseLeft) == ImGuiKeyOwner_NoOwner)
6847 window->WantCollapseToggle = true;
6848 if (window->WantCollapseToggle)
6849 {
6850 window->Collapsed = !window->Collapsed;
6851 if (!window->Collapsed)
6852 use_current_size_for_scrollbar_y = true;
6853 MarkIniSettingsDirty(window);
6854 }
6855 }
6856 else
6857 {
6858 window->Collapsed = false;
6859 }
6860 window->WantCollapseToggle = false;
6861
6862 // SIZE
6863
6864 // Outer Decoration Sizes
6865 // (we need to clear ScrollbarSize immediately as CalcWindowAutoFitSize() needs it and can be called from other locations).
6866 const ImVec2 scrollbar_sizes_from_last_frame = window->ScrollbarSizes;
6867 window->DecoOuterSizeX1 = 0.0f;
6868 window->DecoOuterSizeX2 = 0.0f;
6869 window->DecoOuterSizeY1 = window->TitleBarHeight + window->MenuBarHeight;
6870 window->DecoOuterSizeY2 = 0.0f;
6871 window->ScrollbarSizes = ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f);
6872
6873 // Calculate auto-fit size, handle automatic resize
6874 const ImVec2 size_auto_fit = CalcWindowAutoFitSize(window, window->ContentSizeIdeal);
6875 if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize) && !window->Collapsed)
6876 {
6877 // Using SetNextWindowSize() overrides ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize, so it can be used on tooltips/popups, etc.
6878 if (!window_size_x_set_by_api)
6879 {
6880 window->SizeFull.x = size_auto_fit.x;
6881 use_current_size_for_scrollbar_x = true;
6882 }
6883 if (!window_size_y_set_by_api)
6884 {
6885 window->SizeFull.y = size_auto_fit.y;
6886 use_current_size_for_scrollbar_y = true;
6887 }
6888 }
6889 else if (window->AutoFitFramesX > 0 || window->AutoFitFramesY > 0)
6890 {
6891 // Auto-fit may only grow window during the first few frames
6892 // We still process initial auto-fit on collapsed windows to get a window width, but otherwise don't honor ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize when collapsed.
6893 if (!window_size_x_set_by_api && window->AutoFitFramesX > 0)
6894 {
6895 window->SizeFull.x = window->AutoFitOnlyGrows ? ImMax(window->SizeFull.x, size_auto_fit.x) : size_auto_fit.x;
6896 use_current_size_for_scrollbar_x = true;
6897 }
6898 if (!window_size_y_set_by_api && window->AutoFitFramesY > 0)
6899 {
6900 window->SizeFull.y = window->AutoFitOnlyGrows ? ImMax(window->SizeFull.y, size_auto_fit.y) : size_auto_fit.y;
6901 use_current_size_for_scrollbar_y = true;
6902 }
6903 if (!window->Collapsed)
6904 MarkIniSettingsDirty(window);
6905 }
6906
6907 // Apply minimum/maximum window size constraints and final size
6908 window->SizeFull = CalcWindowSizeAfterConstraint(window, window->SizeFull);
6909 window->Size = window->Collapsed && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) ? window->TitleBarRect().GetSize() : window->SizeFull;
6910
6911 // POSITION
6912
6913 // Popup latch its initial position, will position itself when it appears next frame
6914 if (window_just_activated_by_user)
6915 {
6916 window->AutoPosLastDirection = ImGuiDir_None;
6917 if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) != 0 && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Modal) && !window_pos_set_by_api) // FIXME: BeginPopup() could use SetNextWindowPos()
6918 window->Pos = g.BeginPopupStack.back().OpenPopupPos;
6919 }
6920
6921 // Position child window
6922 if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow)
6923 {
6924 IM_ASSERT(parent_window && parent_window->Active);
6925 window->BeginOrderWithinParent = (short)parent_window->DC.ChildWindows.Size;
6926 parent_window->DC.ChildWindows.push_back(window);
6927 if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) && !window_pos_set_by_api && !window_is_child_tooltip)
6928 window->Pos = parent_window->DC.CursorPos;
6929 }
6930
6931 const bool window_pos_with_pivot = (window->SetWindowPosVal.x != FLT_MAX && window->HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems == 0);
6932 if (window_pos_with_pivot)
6933 SetWindowPos(window, window->SetWindowPosVal - window->Size * window->SetWindowPosPivot, 0); // Position given a pivot (e.g. for centering)
6934 else if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu) != 0)
6935 window->Pos = FindBestWindowPosForPopup(window);
6936 else if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) != 0 && !window_pos_set_by_api && window_just_appearing_after_hidden_for_resize)
6937 window->Pos = FindBestWindowPosForPopup(window);
6938 else if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip) != 0 && !window_pos_set_by_api && !window_is_child_tooltip)
6939 window->Pos = FindBestWindowPosForPopup(window);
6940
6941 // Calculate the range of allowed position for that window (to be movable and visible past safe area padding)
6942 // When clamping to stay visible, we will enforce that window->Pos stays inside of visibility_rect.
6943 ImRect viewport_rect(viewport->GetMainRect());
6944 ImRect viewport_work_rect(viewport->GetWorkRect());
6945 ImVec2 visibility_padding = ImMax(style.DisplayWindowPadding, style.DisplaySafeAreaPadding);
6946 ImRect visibility_rect(viewport_work_rect.Min + visibility_padding, viewport_work_rect.Max - visibility_padding);
6947
6948 // Clamp position/size so window stays visible within its viewport or monitor
6949 // Ignore zero-sized display explicitly to avoid losing positions if a window manager reports zero-sized window when initializing or minimizing.
6950 if (!window_pos_set_by_api && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow))
6951 if (viewport_rect.GetWidth() > 0.0f && viewport_rect.GetHeight() > 0.0f)
6952 ClampWindowPos(window, visibility_rect);
6953 window->Pos = ImTrunc(window->Pos);
6954
6955 // Lock window rounding for the frame (so that altering them doesn't cause inconsistencies)
6956 // Large values tend to lead to variety of artifacts and are not recommended.
6957 window->WindowRounding = (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) ? style.ChildRounding : ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Modal)) ? style.PopupRounding : style.WindowRounding;
6958
6959 // For windows with title bar or menu bar, we clamp to FrameHeight(FontSize + FramePadding.y * 2.0f) to completely hide artifacts.
6960 //if ((window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_MenuBar) || !(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar))
6961 // window->WindowRounding = ImMin(window->WindowRounding, g.FontSize + style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f);
6962
6963 // Apply window focus (new and reactivated windows are moved to front)
6964 bool want_focus = false;
6965 if (window_just_activated_by_user && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoFocusOnAppearing))
6966 {
6967 if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup)
6968 want_focus = true;
6969 else if ((flags & (ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow | ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip)) == 0)
6970 want_focus = true;
6971 }
6972
6973 // [Test Engine] Register whole window in the item system (before submitting further decorations)
6974#ifdef IMGUI_ENABLE_TEST_ENGINE
6975 if (g.TestEngineHookItems)
6976 {
6977 IM_ASSERT(window->IDStack.Size == 1);
6978 window->IDStack.Size = 0; // As window->IDStack[0] == window->ID here, make sure TestEngine doesn't erroneously see window as parent of itself.
6979 IMGUI_TEST_ENGINE_ITEM_ADD(window->ID, window->Rect(), NULL);
6980 IMGUI_TEST_ENGINE_ITEM_INFO(window->ID, window->Name, (g.HoveredWindow == window) ? ImGuiItemStatusFlags_HoveredRect : 0);
6981 window->IDStack.Size = 1;
6982 }
6983#endif
6984
6985 // Handle manual resize: Resize Grips, Borders, Gamepad
6986 int border_hovered = -1, border_held = -1;
6987 ImU32 resize_grip_col[4] = {};
6988 const int resize_grip_count = ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup)) ? 0 : g.IO.ConfigWindowsResizeFromEdges ? 2 : 1; // Allow resize from lower-left if we have the mouse cursor feedback for it.
6989 const float resize_grip_draw_size = IM_TRUNC(ImMax(g.FontSize * 1.10f, window->WindowRounding + 1.0f + g.FontSize * 0.2f));
6990 if (!window->Collapsed)
6991 if (int auto_fit_mask = UpdateWindowManualResize(window, size_auto_fit, &border_hovered, &border_held, resize_grip_count, &resize_grip_col[0], visibility_rect))
6992 {
6993 if (auto_fit_mask & (1 << ImGuiAxis_X))
6994 use_current_size_for_scrollbar_x = true;
6995 if (auto_fit_mask & (1 << ImGuiAxis_Y))
6996 use_current_size_for_scrollbar_y = true;
6997 }
6998 window->ResizeBorderHovered = (signed char)border_hovered;
6999 window->ResizeBorderHeld = (signed char)border_held;
7000
7001 // SCROLLBAR VISIBILITY
7002
7003 // Update scrollbar visibility (based on the Size that was effective during last frame or the auto-resized Size).
7004 if (!window->Collapsed)
7005 {
7006 // When reading the current size we need to read it after size constraints have been applied.
7007 // Intentionally use previous frame values for InnerRect and ScrollbarSizes.
7008 // And when we use window->DecorationUp here it doesn't have ScrollbarSizes.y applied yet.
7009 ImVec2 avail_size_from_current_frame = ImVec2(window->SizeFull.x, window->SizeFull.y - (window->DecoOuterSizeY1 + window->DecoOuterSizeY2));
7010 ImVec2 avail_size_from_last_frame = window->InnerRect.GetSize() + scrollbar_sizes_from_last_frame;
7011 ImVec2 needed_size_from_last_frame = window_just_created ? ImVec2(0, 0) : window->ContentSize + window->WindowPadding * 2.0f;
7012 float size_x_for_scrollbars = use_current_size_for_scrollbar_x ? avail_size_from_current_frame.x : avail_size_from_last_frame.x;
7013 float size_y_for_scrollbars = use_current_size_for_scrollbar_y ? avail_size_from_current_frame.y : avail_size_from_last_frame.y;
7014 //bool scrollbar_y_from_last_frame = window->ScrollbarY; // FIXME: May want to use that in the ScrollbarX expression? How many pros vs cons?
7015 window->ScrollbarY = (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysVerticalScrollbar) || ((needed_size_from_last_frame.y > size_y_for_scrollbars) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar));
7016 window->ScrollbarX = (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysHorizontalScrollbar) || ((needed_size_from_last_frame.x > size_x_for_scrollbars - (window->ScrollbarY ? style.ScrollbarSize : 0.0f)) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar) && (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_HorizontalScrollbar));
7017 if (window->ScrollbarX && !window->ScrollbarY)
7018 window->ScrollbarY = (needed_size_from_last_frame.y > size_y_for_scrollbars - style.ScrollbarSize) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar);
7019 window->ScrollbarSizes = ImVec2(window->ScrollbarY ? style.ScrollbarSize : 0.0f, window->ScrollbarX ? style.ScrollbarSize : 0.0f);
7020
7021 // Amend the partially filled window->DecorationXXX values.
7022 window->DecoOuterSizeX2 += window->ScrollbarSizes.x;
7023 window->DecoOuterSizeY2 += window->ScrollbarSizes.y;
7024 }
7025
7026 // UPDATE RECTANGLES (1- THOSE NOT AFFECTED BY SCROLLING)
7027 // Update various regions. Variables they depend on should be set above in this function.
7028 // We set this up after processing the resize grip so that our rectangles doesn't lag by a frame.
7029
7030 // Outer rectangle
7031 // Not affected by window border size. Used by:
7032 // - FindHoveredWindow() (w/ extra padding when border resize is enabled)
7033 // - Begin() initial clipping rect for drawing window background and borders.
7034 // - Begin() clipping whole child
7035 const ImRect host_rect = ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) && !window_is_child_tooltip) ? parent_window->ClipRect : viewport_rect;
7036 const ImRect outer_rect = window->Rect();
7037 const ImRect title_bar_rect = window->TitleBarRect();
7038 window->OuterRectClipped = outer_rect;
7039 window->OuterRectClipped.ClipWith(host_rect);
7040
7041 // Inner rectangle
7042 // Not affected by window border size. Used by:
7043 // - InnerClipRect
7044 // - ScrollToRectEx()
7045 // - NavUpdatePageUpPageDown()
7046 // - Scrollbar()
7047 window->InnerRect.Min.x = window->Pos.x + window->DecoOuterSizeX1;
7048 window->InnerRect.Min.y = window->Pos.y + window->DecoOuterSizeY1;
7049 window->InnerRect.Max.x = window->Pos.x + window->Size.x - window->DecoOuterSizeX2;
7050 window->InnerRect.Max.y = window->Pos.y + window->Size.y - window->DecoOuterSizeY2;
7051
7052 // Inner clipping rectangle.
7053 // - Extend a outside of normal work region up to borders.
7054 // - This is to allow e.g. Selectable or CollapsingHeader or some separators to cover that space.
7055 // - It also makes clipped items be more noticeable.
7056 // - And is consistent on both axis (prior to 2024/05/03 ClipRect used WindowPadding.x * 0.5f on left and right edge), see #3312
7057 // - Force round operator last to ensure that e.g. (int)(max.x-min.x) in user's render code produce correct result.
7058 // Note that if our window is collapsed we will end up with an inverted (~null) clipping rectangle which is the correct behavior.
7059 // Affected by window/frame border size. Used by:
7060 // - Begin() initial clip rect
7061 float top_border_size = (((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_MenuBar) || !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar)) ? style.FrameBorderSize : window->WindowBorderSize);
7062 window->InnerClipRect.Min.x = ImFloor(0.5f + window->InnerRect.Min.x + window->WindowBorderSize);
7063 window->InnerClipRect.Min.y = ImFloor(0.5f + window->InnerRect.Min.y + top_border_size);
7064 window->InnerClipRect.Max.x = ImFloor(0.5f + window->InnerRect.Max.x - window->WindowBorderSize);
7065 window->InnerClipRect.Max.y = ImFloor(0.5f + window->InnerRect.Max.y - window->WindowBorderSize);
7066 window->InnerClipRect.ClipWithFull(host_rect);
7067
7068 // Default item width. Make it proportional to window size if window manually resizes
7069 if (window->Size.x > 0.0f && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Tooltip) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_AlwaysAutoResize))
7070 window->ItemWidthDefault = ImTrunc(window->Size.x * 0.65f);
7071 else
7072 window->ItemWidthDefault = ImTrunc(g.FontSize * 16.0f);
7073
7074 // SCROLLING
7075
7076 // Lock down maximum scrolling
7077 // The value of ScrollMax are ahead from ScrollbarX/ScrollbarY which is intentionally using InnerRect from previous rect in order to accommodate
7078 // for right/bottom aligned items without creating a scrollbar.
7079 window->ScrollMax.x = ImMax(0.0f, window->ContentSize.x + window->WindowPadding.x * 2.0f - window->InnerRect.GetWidth());
7080 window->ScrollMax.y = ImMax(0.0f, window->ContentSize.y + window->WindowPadding.y * 2.0f - window->InnerRect.GetHeight());
7081
7082 // Apply scrolling
7083 window->Scroll = CalcNextScrollFromScrollTargetAndClamp(window);
7084 window->ScrollTarget = ImVec2(FLT_MAX, FLT_MAX);
7085 window->DecoInnerSizeX1 = window->DecoInnerSizeY1 = 0.0f;
7086
7087 // DRAWING
7088
7089 // Setup draw list and outer clipping rectangle
7090 IM_ASSERT(window->DrawList->CmdBuffer.Size == 1 && window->DrawList->CmdBuffer[0].ElemCount == 0);
7091 window->DrawList->PushTextureID(g.Font->ContainerAtlas->TexID);
7092 PushClipRect(host_rect.Min, host_rect.Max, false);
7093
7094 // Child windows can render their decoration (bg color, border, scrollbars, etc.) within their parent to save a draw call (since 1.71)
7095 // When using overlapping child windows, this will break the assumption that child z-order is mapped to submission order.
7096 // FIXME: User code may rely on explicit sorting of overlapping child window and would need to disable this somehow. Please get in contact if you are affected (github #4493)
7097 {
7098 bool render_decorations_in_parent = false;
7099 if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Popup) && !window_is_child_tooltip)
7100 {
7101 // - We test overlap with the previous child window only (testing all would end up being O(log N) not a good investment here)
7102 // - We disable this when the parent window has zero vertices, which is a common pattern leading to laying out multiple overlapping childs
7103 ImGuiWindow* previous_child = parent_window->DC.ChildWindows.Size >= 2 ? parent_window->DC.ChildWindows[parent_window->DC.ChildWindows.Size - 2] : NULL;
7104 bool previous_child_overlapping = previous_child ? previous_child->Rect().Overlaps(window->Rect()) : false;
7105 bool parent_is_empty = (parent_window->DrawList->VtxBuffer.Size == 0);
7106 if (window->DrawList->CmdBuffer.back().ElemCount == 0 && !parent_is_empty && !previous_child_overlapping)
7107 render_decorations_in_parent = true;
7108 }
7109 if (render_decorations_in_parent)
7110 window->DrawList = parent_window->DrawList;
7111
7112 // Handle title bar, scrollbar, resize grips and resize borders
7113 const ImGuiWindow* window_to_highlight = g.NavWindowingTarget ? g.NavWindowingTarget : g.NavWindow;
7114 const bool title_bar_is_highlight = want_focus || (window_to_highlight && window->RootWindowForTitleBarHighlight == window_to_highlight->RootWindowForTitleBarHighlight);
7115 const bool handle_borders_and_resize_grips = true; // This exists to facilitate merge with 'docking' branch.
7116 RenderWindowDecorations(window, title_bar_rect, title_bar_is_highlight, handle_borders_and_resize_grips, resize_grip_count, resize_grip_col, resize_grip_draw_size);
7117
7118 if (render_decorations_in_parent)
7119 window->DrawList = &window->DrawListInst;
7120 }
7121
7122 // UPDATE RECTANGLES (2- THOSE AFFECTED BY SCROLLING)
7123
7124 // Work rectangle.
7125 // Affected by window padding and border size. Used by:
7126 // - Columns() for right-most edge
7127 // - TreeNode(), CollapsingHeader() for right-most edge
7128 // - BeginTabBar() for right-most edge
7129 const bool allow_scrollbar_x = !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar) && (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_HorizontalScrollbar);
7130 const bool allow_scrollbar_y = !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollbar);
7131 const float work_rect_size_x = (window->ContentSizeExplicit.x != 0.0f ? window->ContentSizeExplicit.x : ImMax(allow_scrollbar_x ? window->ContentSize.x : 0.0f, window->Size.x - window->WindowPadding.x * 2.0f - (window->DecoOuterSizeX1 + window->DecoOuterSizeX2)));
7132 const float work_rect_size_y = (window->ContentSizeExplicit.y != 0.0f ? window->ContentSizeExplicit.y : ImMax(allow_scrollbar_y ? window->ContentSize.y : 0.0f, window->Size.y - window->WindowPadding.y * 2.0f - (window->DecoOuterSizeY1 + window->DecoOuterSizeY2)));
7133 window->WorkRect.Min.x = ImTrunc(window->InnerRect.Min.x - window->Scroll.x + ImMax(window->WindowPadding.x, window->WindowBorderSize));
7134 window->WorkRect.Min.y = ImTrunc(window->InnerRect.Min.y - window->Scroll.y + ImMax(window->WindowPadding.y, window->WindowBorderSize));
7135 window->WorkRect.Max.x = window->WorkRect.Min.x + work_rect_size_x;
7136 window->WorkRect.Max.y = window->WorkRect.Min.y + work_rect_size_y;
7137 window->ParentWorkRect = window->WorkRect;
7138
7139 // [LEGACY] Content Region
7140 // FIXME-OBSOLETE: window->ContentRegionRect.Max is currently very misleading / partly faulty, but some BeginChild() patterns relies on it.
7141 // Unless explicit content size is specified by user, this currently represent the region leading to no scrolling.
7142 // Used by:
7143 // - Mouse wheel scrolling + many other things
7144 window->ContentRegionRect.Min.x = window->Pos.x - window->Scroll.x + window->WindowPadding.x + window->DecoOuterSizeX1;
7145 window->ContentRegionRect.Min.y = window->Pos.y - window->Scroll.y + window->WindowPadding.y + window->DecoOuterSizeY1;
7146 window->ContentRegionRect.Max.x = window->ContentRegionRect.Min.x + (window->ContentSizeExplicit.x != 0.0f ? window->ContentSizeExplicit.x : (window->Size.x - window->WindowPadding.x * 2.0f - (window->DecoOuterSizeX1 + window->DecoOuterSizeX2)));
7147 window->ContentRegionRect.Max.y = window->ContentRegionRect.Min.y + (window->ContentSizeExplicit.y != 0.0f ? window->ContentSizeExplicit.y : (window->Size.y - window->WindowPadding.y * 2.0f - (window->DecoOuterSizeY1 + window->DecoOuterSizeY2)));
7148
7149 // Setup drawing context
7150 // (NB: That term "drawing context / DC" lost its meaning a long time ago. Initially was meant to hold transient data only. Nowadays difference between window-> and window->DC-> is dubious.)
7151 window->DC.Indent.x = window->DecoOuterSizeX1 + window->WindowPadding.x - window->Scroll.x;
7152 window->DC.GroupOffset.x = 0.0f;
7153 window->DC.ColumnsOffset.x = 0.0f;
7154
7155 // Record the loss of precision of CursorStartPos which can happen due to really large scrolling amount.
7156 // This is used by clipper to compensate and fix the most common use case of large scroll area. Easy and cheap, next best thing compared to switching everything to double or ImU64.
7157 double start_pos_highp_x = (double)window->Pos.x + window->WindowPadding.x - (double)window->Scroll.x + window->DecoOuterSizeX1 + window->DC.ColumnsOffset.x;
7158 double start_pos_highp_y = (double)window->Pos.y + window->WindowPadding.y - (double)window->Scroll.y + window->DecoOuterSizeY1;
7159 window->DC.CursorStartPos = ImVec2((float)start_pos_highp_x, (float)start_pos_highp_y);
7160 window->DC.CursorStartPosLossyness = ImVec2((float)(start_pos_highp_x - window->DC.CursorStartPos.x), (float)(start_pos_highp_y - window->DC.CursorStartPos.y));
7161 window->DC.CursorPos = window->DC.CursorStartPos;
7162 window->DC.CursorPosPrevLine = window->DC.CursorPos;
7163 window->DC.CursorMaxPos = window->DC.CursorStartPos;
7164 window->DC.IdealMaxPos = window->DC.CursorStartPos;
7165 window->DC.CurrLineSize = window->DC.PrevLineSize = ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f);
7166 window->DC.CurrLineTextBaseOffset = window->DC.PrevLineTextBaseOffset = 0.0f;
7167 window->DC.IsSameLine = window->DC.IsSetPos = false;
7168
7169 window->DC.NavLayerCurrent = ImGuiNavLayer_Main;
7170 window->DC.NavLayersActiveMask = window->DC.NavLayersActiveMaskNext;
7171 window->DC.NavLayersActiveMaskNext = 0x00;
7172 window->DC.NavIsScrollPushableX = true;
7173 window->DC.NavHideHighlightOneFrame = false;
7174 window->DC.NavWindowHasScrollY = (window->ScrollMax.y > 0.0f);
7175
7176 window->DC.MenuBarAppending = false;
7177 window->DC.MenuColumns.Update(style.ItemSpacing.x, window_just_activated_by_user);
7178 window->DC.TreeDepth = 0;
7179 window->DC.TreeHasStackDataDepthMask = 0x00;
7180 window->DC.ChildWindows.resize(0);
7181 window->DC.StateStorage = &window->StateStorage;
7182 window->DC.CurrentColumns = NULL;
7183 window->DC.LayoutType = ImGuiLayoutType_Vertical;
7184 window->DC.ParentLayoutType = parent_window ? parent_window->DC.LayoutType : ImGuiLayoutType_Vertical;
7185
7186 window->DC.ItemWidth = window->ItemWidthDefault;
7187 window->DC.TextWrapPos = -1.0f; // disabled
7188 window->DC.ItemWidthStack.resize(0);
7189 window->DC.TextWrapPosStack.resize(0);
7190 if (flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_Modal)
7191 window->DC.ModalDimBgColor = ColorConvertFloat4ToU32(GetStyleColorVec4(ImGuiCol_ModalWindowDimBg));
7192
7193 if (window->AutoFitFramesX > 0)
7194 window->AutoFitFramesX--;
7195 if (window->AutoFitFramesY > 0)
7196 window->AutoFitFramesY--;
7197
7198 // Apply focus (we need to call FocusWindow() AFTER setting DC.CursorStartPos so our initial navigation reference rectangle can start around there)
7199 // We ImGuiFocusRequestFlags_UnlessBelowModal to:
7200 // - Avoid focusing a window that is created outside of a modal. This will prevent active modal from being closed.
7201 // - Position window behind the modal that is not a begin-parent of this window.
7202 if (want_focus)
7203 FocusWindow(window, ImGuiFocusRequestFlags_UnlessBelowModal);
7204 if (want_focus && window == g.NavWindow)
7205 NavInitWindow(window, false); // <-- this is in the way for us to be able to defer and sort reappearing FocusWindow() calls
7206
7207 // Title bar
7208 if (!(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar))
7209 RenderWindowTitleBarContents(window, ImRect(title_bar_rect.Min.x + window->WindowBorderSize, title_bar_rect.Min.y, title_bar_rect.Max.x - window->WindowBorderSize, title_bar_rect.Max.y), name, p_open);
7210
7211 // Clear hit test shape every frame
7212 window->HitTestHoleSize.x = window->HitTestHoleSize.y = 0;
7213
7214 // Pressing CTRL+C while holding on a window copy its content to the clipboard
7215 // This works but 1. doesn't handle multiple Begin/End pairs, 2. recursing into another Begin/End pair - so we need to work that out and add better logging scope.
7216 // Maybe we can support CTRL+C on every element?
7217 /*
7218 //if (g.NavWindow == window && g.ActiveId == 0)
7219 if (g.ActiveId == window->MoveId)
7220 if (g.IO.KeyCtrl && IsKeyPressed(ImGuiKey_C))
7221 LogToClipboard();
7222 */
7223
7224 // We fill last item data based on Title Bar/Tab, in order for IsItemHovered() and IsItemActive() to be usable after Begin().
7225 // This is useful to allow creating context menus on title bar only, etc.
7226 SetLastItemDataForWindow(window, title_bar_rect);
7227
7228 // [DEBUG]
7229#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_DEBUG_TOOLS
7230 if (g.DebugLocateId != 0 && (window->ID == g.DebugLocateId || window->MoveId == g.DebugLocateId))
7231 DebugLocateItemResolveWithLastItem();
7232#endif
7233
7234 // [Test Engine] Register title bar / tab with MoveId.
7235#ifdef IMGUI_ENABLE_TEST_ENGINE
7236 if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar))
7237 IMGUI_TEST_ENGINE_ITEM_ADD(g.LastItemData.ID, g.LastItemData.Rect, &g.LastItemData);
7238#endif
7239 }
7240 else
7241 {
7242 // Skip refresh always mark active
7243 if (window->SkipRefresh)
7244 window->Active = true;
7245
7246 // Append
7247 SetCurrentWindow(window);
7248 SetLastItemDataForWindow(window, window->TitleBarRect());
7249 }
7250
7251 if (!window->SkipRefresh)
7252 PushClipRect(window->InnerClipRect.Min, window->InnerClipRect.Max, true);
7253
7254 // Clear 'accessed' flag last thing (After PushClipRect which will set the flag. We want the flag to stay false when the default "Debug" window is unused)
7255 window->WriteAccessed = false;
7256 window->BeginCount++;
7257 g.NextWindowData.ClearFlags();
7258
7259 // Update visibility
7260 if (first_begin_of_the_frame && !window->SkipRefresh)
7261 {
7262 if ((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildWindow) && !(flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_ChildMenu))
7263 {
7264 // Child window can be out of sight and have "negative" clip windows.
7265 // Mark them as collapsed so commands are skipped earlier (we can't manually collapse them because they have no title bar).
7266 IM_ASSERT((flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) != 0);
7267 const bool nav_request = (window->ChildFlags & ImGuiChildFlags_NavFlattened) && (g.NavAnyRequest && g.NavWindow && g.NavWindow->RootWindowForNav == window->RootWindowForNav);
7268 if (!g.LogEnabled && !nav_request)
7269 if (window->OuterRectClipped.Min.x >= window->OuterRectClipped.Max.x || window->OuterRectClipped.Min.y >= window->OuterRectClipped.Max.y)
7270 {
7271 if (window->AutoFitFramesX > 0 || window->AutoFitFramesY > 0)
7272 window->HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems = 1;
7273 else
7274 window->HiddenFramesCanSkipItems = 1;
7275 }
7276
7277 // Hide along with parent or if parent is collapsed
7278 if (parent_window && (parent_window->Collapsed || parent_window->HiddenFramesCanSkipItems > 0))
7279 window->HiddenFramesCanSkipItems = 1;
7280 if (parent_window && (parent_window->Collapsed || parent_window->HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems > 0))
7281 window->HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems = 1;
7282 }
7283
7284 // Don't render if style alpha is 0.0 at the time of Begin(). This is arbitrary and inconsistent but has been there for a long while (may remove at some point)
7285 if (style.Alpha <= 0.0f)
7286 window->HiddenFramesCanSkipItems = 1;
7287
7288 // Update the Hidden flag
7289 bool hidden_regular = (window->HiddenFramesCanSkipItems > 0) || (window->HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems > 0);
7290 window->Hidden = hidden_regular || (window->HiddenFramesForRenderOnly > 0);
7291
7292 // Disable inputs for requested number of frames
7293 if (window->DisableInputsFrames > 0)
7294 {
7295 window->DisableInputsFrames--;
7296 window->Flags |= ImGuiWindowFlags_NoInputs;
7297 }
7298
7299 // Update the SkipItems flag, used to early out of all items functions (no layout required)
7300 bool skip_items = false;
7301 if (window->Collapsed || !window->Active || hidden_regular)
7302 if (window->AutoFitFramesX <= 0 && window->AutoFitFramesY <= 0 && window->HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems <= 0)
7303 skip_items = true;
7304 window->SkipItems = skip_items;
7305 }
7306 else if (first_begin_of_the_frame)
7307 {
7308 // Skip refresh mode
7309 window->SkipItems = true;
7310 }
7311
7312 // [DEBUG] io.ConfigDebugBeginReturnValue override return value to test Begin/End and BeginChild/EndChild behaviors.
7313 // (The implicit fallback window is NOT automatically ended allowing it to always be able to receive commands without crashing)
7314#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_DEBUG_TOOLS
7315 if (!window->IsFallbackWindow)
7316 if ((g.IO.ConfigDebugBeginReturnValueOnce && window_just_created) || (g.IO.ConfigDebugBeginReturnValueLoop && g.DebugBeginReturnValueCullDepth == g.CurrentWindowStack.Size))
7317 {
7318 if (window->AutoFitFramesX > 0) { window->AutoFitFramesX++; }
7319 if (window->AutoFitFramesY > 0) { window->AutoFitFramesY++; }
7320 return false;
7321 }
7322#endif
7323
7324 return !window->SkipItems;
7325}

10017{

10020 // Verify that io.KeyXXX fields haven't been tampered with. Key mods should not be modified between NewFrame() and EndFrame()
10021 // One possible reason leading to this assert is that your backends update inputs _AFTER_ NewFrame().
10022 // It is known that when some modal native windows called mid-frame takes focus away, some backends such as GLFW will
10023 // send key release events mid-frame. This would normally trigger this assertion and lead to sheared inputs.
10024 // We silently accommodate for this case by ignoring the case where all io.KeyXXX modifiers were released (aka key_mod_flags == 0),
10025 // while still correctly asserting on mid-frame key press events.
10026 const ImGuiKeyChord key_mods = GetMergedModsFromKeys();

10034 // to always call End/EndChild even if Begin/BeginChild returns false! (this is unfortunately inconsistent with most other Begin* API).
10035 if (g.CurrentWindowStack.Size != 1)
10036 {

11771 // One typical case where this happens, with style.WindowMenuButtonPosition == ImGuiDir_Right, pressing Left to navigate from Close to Collapse tends to fail.

11857 // This is just to avoid buttons having no links in a particular direction when there's a suitable neighbor. you get good graphs without this too.
11858 // 2017/09/29: FIXME: This now currently only enabled inside menu bars, ideally we'd disable it everywhere. Menus in particular need to catch failure. For general navigation it feels awkward.

11863 {
11864 result->DistAxial = dist_axial;
11865 new_best = true;
11866 }

11868 return new_best;

12574 bool clamp_y = (g.NavMoveFlags & (ImGuiNavMoveFlags_LoopY | ImGuiNavMoveFlags_WrapY)) == 0;
12575 ImRect inner_rect_rel = WindowRectAbsToRel(window, ImRect(window->InnerRect.Min - ImVec2(1, 1), window->InnerRect.Max + ImVec2(1, 1)));
12576
12577 // Take account of changing scroll to handle triggering a new move request on a scrolling frame. (#6171)
12578 // Otherwise 'inner_rect_rel' would be off on the move result frame.
12579 inner_rect_rel.Translate(CalcNextScrollFromScrollTargetAndClamp(window) - window->Scroll);
12580
12581 if ((clamp_x || clamp_y) && !inner_rect_rel.Contains(window->NavRectRel[g.NavLayer]))
12582 {
12583 IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_NAV("[nav] NavMoveRequest: clamp NavRectRel for gamepad move\n");
12584 float pad_x = ImMin(inner_rect_rel.GetWidth(), window->CalcFontSize() * 0.5f);
12585 float pad_y = ImMin(inner_rect_rel.GetHeight(), window->CalcFontSize() * 0.5f); // Terrible approximation for the intent of starting navigation from first fully visible item
12586 inner_rect_rel.Min.x = clamp_x ? (inner_rect_rel.Min.x + pad_x) : -FLT_MAX;
12587 inner_rect_rel.Max.x = clamp_x ? (inner_rect_rel.Max.x - pad_x) : +FLT_MAX;
12588 inner_rect_rel.Min.y = clamp_y ? (inner_rect_rel.Min.y + pad_y) : -FLT_MAX;
12589 inner_rect_rel.Max.y = clamp_y ? (inner_rect_rel.Max.y - pad_y) : +FLT_MAX;
12590 window->NavRectRel[g.NavLayer].ClipWithFull(inner_rect_rel);
12591 g.NavId = 0;
12592 }
12593 }
12594
12595 // For scoring we use a single segment on the left side our current item bounding box (not touching the edge to avoid box overlap with zero-spaced items)
12596 ImRect scoring_rect;
12597 if (window != NULL)
12598 {
12599 ImRect nav_rect_rel = !window->NavRectRel[g.NavLayer].IsInverted() ? window->NavRectRel[g.NavLayer] : ImRect(0, 0, 0, 0);
12600 scoring_rect = WindowRectRelToAbs(window, nav_rect_rel);
12601 scoring_rect.TranslateY(scoring_rect_offset_y);
12602 if (g.NavMoveSubmitted)
12603 NavBiasScoringRect(scoring_rect, window->RootWindowForNav->NavPreferredScoringPosRel[g.NavLayer], g.NavMoveDir, g.NavMoveFlags);
12604 IM_ASSERT(!scoring_rect.IsInverted()); // Ensure we have a non-inverted bounding box here will allow us to remove extraneous ImFabs() calls in NavScoreItem().
12605 //GetForegroundDrawList()->AddRect(scoring_rect.Min, scoring_rect.Max, IM_COL32(255,200,0,255)); // [DEBUG]
12606 //if (!g.NavScoringNoClipRect.IsInverted()) { GetForegroundDrawList()->AddRect(g.NavScoringNoClipRect.Min, g.NavScoringNoClipRect.Max, IM_COL32(255, 200, 0, 255)); } // [DEBUG]
12607 }
12608 g.NavScoringRect = scoring_rect;
12609 g.NavScoringNoClipRect.Add(scoring_rect);

14776 static ImRect GetWindowRect(ImGuiWindow* window, int rect_type)
14777 {
14778 if (rect_type == WRT_OuterRect) { return window->Rect(); }
14779 else if (rect_type == WRT_OuterRectClipped) { return window->OuterRectClipped; }
14780 else if (rect_type == WRT_InnerRect) { return window->InnerRect; }
14781 else if (rect_type == WRT_InnerClipRect) { return window->InnerClipRect; }
14782 else if (rect_type == WRT_WorkRect) { return window->WorkRect; }
14783 else if (rect_type == WRT_Content) { ImVec2 min = window->InnerRect.Min - window->Scroll + window->WindowPadding; return ImRect(min, min + window->ContentSize); }
14784 else if (rect_type == WRT_ContentIdeal) { ImVec2 min = window->InnerRect.Min - window->Scroll + window->WindowPadding; return ImRect(min, min + window->ContentSizeIdeal); }
14785 else if (rect_type == WRT_ContentRegionRect) { return window->ContentRegionRect; }
14786 IM_ASSERT(0);
14787 return ImRect();

9477 if (wheel.y != 0.0f && g.IO.KeyCtrl && g.IO.FontAllowUserScaling)
9478 {
9479 LockWheelingWindow(mouse_window, wheel.y);
9480 ImGuiWindow* window = mouse_window;
9481 const float new_font_scale = ImClamp(window->FontWindowScale + g.IO.MouseWheel * 0.10f, 0.50f, 2.50f);
9482 const float scale = new_font_scale / window->FontWindowScale;
9483 window->FontWindowScale = new_font_scale;
9484 if (window == window->RootWindow)
9485 {
9486 const ImVec2 offset = window->Size * (1.0f - scale) * (g.IO.MousePos - window->Pos) / window->Size;
9487 SetWindowPos(window, window->Pos + offset, 0);
9488 window->Size = ImTrunc(window->Size * scale);
9489 window->SizeFull = ImTrunc(window->SizeFull * scale);
9490 }
9491 return;
9492 }
9493 if (g.IO.KeyCtrl)
9494 return;
9495
9496 // Mouse wheel scrolling
9497 // Read about io.MouseWheelRequestAxisSwap and its issue on Mac+Emscripten in UpdateMouseInputs()
9498 if (g.IO.MouseWheelRequestAxisSwap)
9499 wheel = ImVec2(wheel.y, 0.0f);
9500
9501 // Maintain a rough average of moving magnitude on both axises
9502 // FIXME: should by based on wall clock time rather than frame-counter
9503 g.WheelingAxisAvg.x = ImExponentialMovingAverage(g.WheelingAxisAvg.x, ImAbs(wheel.x), 30);
9504 g.WheelingAxisAvg.y = ImExponentialMovingAverage(g.WheelingAxisAvg.y, ImAbs(wheel.y), 30);
9505
9506 // In the rare situation where FindBestWheelingWindow() had to defer first frame of wheeling due to ambiguous main axis, reinject it now.
9507 wheel += g.WheelingWindowWheelRemainder;
9508 g.WheelingWindowWheelRemainder = ImVec2(0.0f, 0.0f);
9509 if (wheel.x == 0.0f && wheel.y == 0.0f)
9510 return;
9511
9512 // Mouse wheel scrolling: find target and apply
9513 // - don't renew lock if axis doesn't apply on the window.
9514 // - select a main axis when both axises are being moved.
9515 if (ImGuiWindow* window = (g.WheelingWindow ? g.WheelingWindow : FindBestWheelingWindow(wheel)))
9516 if (!(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoScrollWithMouse) && !(window->Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoMouseInputs))
9517 {
9518 bool do_scroll[2] = { wheel.x != 0.0f && window->ScrollMax.x != 0.0f, wheel.y != 0.0f && window->ScrollMax.y != 0.0f };
9519 if (do_scroll[ImGuiAxis_X] && do_scroll[ImGuiAxis_Y])
9520 do_scroll[(g.WheelingAxisAvg.x > g.WheelingAxisAvg.y) ? ImGuiAxis_Y : ImGuiAxis_X] = false;
9521 if (do_scroll[ImGuiAxis_X])
9522 {
9523 LockWheelingWindow(window, wheel.x);
9524 float max_step = window->InnerRect.GetWidth() * 0.67f;
9525 float scroll_step = ImTrunc(ImMin(2 * window->CalcFontSize(), max_step));
9526 SetScrollX(window, window->Scroll.x - wheel.x * scroll_step);
9527 g.WheelingWindowScrolledFrame = g.FrameCount;
9528 }
9529 if (do_scroll[ImGuiAxis_Y])
9530 {
9531 LockWheelingWindow(window, wheel.y);
9532 float max_step = window->InnerRect.GetHeight() * 0.67f;
9533 float scroll_step = ImTrunc(ImMin(5 * window->CalcFontSize(), max_step));
9534 SetScrollY(window, window->Scroll.y - wheel.y * scroll_step);
9535 g.WheelingWindowScrolledFrame = g.FrameCount;
9536 }
9537 }
